WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:02.234
<i>Amy: Previously on "heartland":</i>

00:02.303 --> 00:04.169
- I mean, I make it a firm rule
not to date anyone

00:04.238 --> 00:05.871
I'm in business with.

00:06.006 --> 00:09.474
Sorry, that was my clumsy segue
to asking you out.

00:10.511 --> 00:12.511
Lou, help!
- Fred!

00:12.513 --> 00:15.748
- Help! Help, lou!
- You got it!

00:15.883 --> 00:17.549
- You know you saved
their lives.

00:17.551 --> 00:19.051
Thank you, sam,

00:19.120 --> 00:21.386
For everything.
- Yeah, no worries.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.122
- When you're ready,
you just let me know.

00:23.257 --> 00:24.790
- Mm-hmm.

00:24.792 --> 00:26.157
- And I'll be with you
in a heartbeat.

00:26.193 --> 00:27.793
- Okay.

00:27.795 --> 00:29.461
<i> Georgie: You can treat</i>
<i> his arthritis.</i>

00:29.463 --> 00:31.864
<i> Amy: I know, but he's never</i>
<i> gonna be like he was.</i>

00:31.866 --> 00:33.164
<i> I think I've known that</i>
<i> for a while.</i>

00:33.200 --> 00:36.268
<i> I... I just didn't wanna</i>
<i> believe it.</i>

00:38.639 --> 00:47.946
♪♪♪

00:47.948 --> 00:49.014
Good boy, spartan.

00:49.149 --> 00:52.584
(hooves thud,
grass crunches)

00:52.620 --> 00:55.553
(hooves thud heavily)

00:55.589 --> 01:00.058
♪♪♪

01:00.061 --> 01:01.960
(spartan grunts)

01:02.096 --> 01:04.028
(spartan nickers)

01:04.065 --> 01:07.766
Come on, spartan. It's okay.
Come on, let's go.

01:07.768 --> 01:10.035
(spartan grunts)
- hey, hey, it's okay.

01:10.170 --> 01:13.238
What's wrong?
- (spartan grunts)

01:13.240 --> 01:15.039
- You're hurting, aren't you?

01:15.076 --> 01:17.442
- (spartan grunts)
- yeah.

01:17.445 --> 01:20.112
- (spartan nickers)
- I know, it's okay.

01:21.415 --> 01:22.981
We don't have to go up there.

01:23.117 --> 01:25.049
- (spartan grunts)
- let's walk home, okay?

01:25.086 --> 01:26.251
Come on.

01:26.287 --> 01:28.486
(birds chirp,
hooves thud)

01:29.790 --> 01:31.123
(amy sighs)
jessica: Thanks, ezra.

01:31.258 --> 01:32.991
Yeah, I'll text you
when I get to town.

01:33.127 --> 01:35.727
Okay, all right.
You're the best.

01:35.729 --> 01:38.396
(footsteps approach)
- hey.

01:38.432 --> 01:39.797
- Hey!
- Who was that?

01:39.834 --> 01:41.200
- Oh, that's my friend, ezra.

01:41.202 --> 01:43.535
He's helping me wrap up
a few things in new york

01:43.537 --> 01:48.072
And make sure my condo sale
goes off without a hitch.

01:48.109 --> 01:50.008
- Well, good for ezra.

01:50.144 --> 01:52.277
Sounds like a great guy.

01:52.346 --> 01:56.315
- Mr. Fleming, do I detect
a little bit of jealousy?

01:56.317 --> 01:59.418
- Well, he's kinda going
out of his way to help ya.

01:59.553 --> 02:01.587
- Oh, trust me, you have
nothing to worry about.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.555
We dated for a while years ago,

02:03.690 --> 02:05.224
But we are better off
as friends.

02:05.226 --> 02:08.993
- And you dated.
(jessica's phone rings)

02:09.029 --> 02:10.562
- Hey, ez.

02:10.564 --> 02:13.165
Yeah, no, no, you don't need
to pick me up from the airport.

02:13.234 --> 02:14.933
Okay, sure.

02:15.002 --> 02:16.768
Yeah, I mean, it'll save me
the uber drive.

02:16.904 --> 02:19.037
Okay, all right.
I'll see you in a few days.

02:19.172 --> 02:20.205
Okay, bye.

02:20.241 --> 02:21.907
(phone clicks off)

02:22.042 --> 02:25.043
♪♪♪

02:25.045 --> 02:27.012
(engine rumbles to a stop)

02:28.249 --> 02:31.015
(engine turns off,
doors click open and shut)

02:32.353 --> 02:34.118
Amy: Okay, come on, sweetheart!

02:34.155 --> 02:35.154
Can you get out?

02:37.858 --> 02:39.258
I thought you said we were
meeting them here.

02:39.260 --> 02:41.927
- Yeah, but you were late,
so they must've gone on ahead.

02:41.996 --> 02:44.462
- I'm sorry, but spartan's
arthritis was acting up

02:44.498 --> 02:46.198
And I had to walk him
all the way home.

02:46.267 --> 02:47.933
<i> (chainsaw buzzes nearby)</i>

02:47.935 --> 02:51.069
- Oh. Sounds like they're
that way.

02:51.071 --> 02:53.338
- Let's go! I wanna see
the giant horse!

02:53.407 --> 02:55.474
- Okay.

02:55.476 --> 02:57.276
That way. Oh.

02:57.278 --> 02:59.278
(butch nickers)
lyndy: There he is!

02:59.280 --> 03:01.012
- Awww...

03:01.048 --> 03:02.447
(hooves thud heavily,
harness jingles)

03:02.583 --> 03:04.216
- Whoa...
(butch nickers)

03:05.319 --> 03:07.819
- Hey, uh, al?

03:07.821 --> 03:09.287
- Oh, yeah, hi.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.889
- Uh, thanks for letting us
come and see you in action.

03:13.093 --> 03:15.761
- Well, not much to see, really.

03:15.896 --> 03:17.196
- Don't be modest.
I've heard all about

03:17.331 --> 03:19.865
Your impressive winning streak
in the draft horse races.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.400
It's gonna be the perfect
halftime show

03:21.402 --> 03:23.134
For the lumberjack competition.

03:23.204 --> 03:25.070
- I see ya already
brought a crowd.

03:25.205 --> 03:27.105
- (chuckles)
- this is my sister, amy,

03:27.241 --> 03:28.974
And her daughter, lyndy.

03:30.110 --> 03:33.645
- Ah. She's named after
your grandma, huh?

03:33.780 --> 03:35.880
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I knew her.

03:36.951 --> 03:39.484
And jack.
- Huh.

03:39.486 --> 03:42.420
- Uh, this-this
is my grandson, finn.

03:42.422 --> 03:44.990
- It's nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

03:44.992 --> 03:47.326
I think it's really great
that you're doing

03:47.328 --> 03:49.861
This heritage way of logging.
- Well...

03:49.897 --> 03:51.863
- And that you're keeping it
in the family.

03:51.999 --> 03:53.865
- I'm, I'm just helping out
for the day.

03:53.901 --> 03:55.334
- Yeah, finn's from
saskatchewan.

03:55.336 --> 03:57.935
He's comin' to keep an eye
on the old man.

03:57.972 --> 03:59.671
- Well, you know, we do need
some more competitors

03:59.806 --> 04:01.406
In the competition...

04:01.408 --> 04:03.108
Since you grew up around this?
- I'm not...

04:03.243 --> 04:06.745
- Yeah, he'll do it.
- Grandpa... (chuckles)

04:06.747 --> 04:09.014
- Well, I'm too old to take
part in the other events.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.516
Someone's gotta represent
the family name, right?

04:11.552 --> 04:14.019
- (snorts) I guess I'm in.
- Great!

04:14.088 --> 04:15.353
- Well, can you show us
a little

04:15.422 --> 04:17.022
Of what you'll do this weekend?

04:17.157 --> 04:19.223
(butch grunts)
- sure.

04:19.260 --> 04:22.627
I'll, uh, I'll wind him
through a few trees there

04:22.763 --> 04:25.430
And take him between
those two aspens.

04:25.499 --> 04:27.232
- He's gonna fit between there?

04:27.234 --> 04:29.601
- Oh yeah,
while he's draggin' a log!

04:29.736 --> 04:32.671
Come on, fella,
show 'em what we can do.

04:32.673 --> 04:33.505
(hooves thud heavily)

04:33.574 --> 04:36.708
(chain jingles,
log rumbles)

04:37.978 --> 04:39.511
(butch neighs)

04:39.513 --> 04:44.149
♪♪♪

04:44.284 --> 04:45.684
- Get up!
(butch grunts)

04:45.819 --> 04:48.920
- Steady.
(butch whinnies wildly)

04:50.090 --> 04:52.056
- Whoa, boy!
(heavy thump) agh!

04:52.058 --> 04:54.159
Oh! (groans)
- grandpa!

04:54.161 --> 04:56.862
- Agh! I'm fine, I'm fine!

04:56.997 --> 04:59.798
- Whoa... Steady, butch. Whoa...

04:59.867 --> 05:01.466
(al groans and pants)

05:02.736 --> 05:04.869
- What's wrong with the horse,
mommy?

05:04.938 --> 05:07.072
- (sighs) I'm not sure, honey.

05:08.309 --> 05:10.075
- Oh, you poor old thing.

05:10.144 --> 05:13.211
Butch, come on!
You can do better than that.

05:15.849 --> 05:23.855
♪♪♪

05:23.857 --> 05:30.962
♪♪♪

05:31.031 --> 05:33.464
♪ and at the break of day ♪

05:33.500 --> 05:36.701
♪ you sank into your dream ♪

05:38.271 --> 05:39.571
♪ you dreamer ♪

05:39.573 --> 05:42.240
♪ oh, oh, oh, oh... ♪

05:42.309 --> 05:43.942
♪ you dreamer ♪

05:46.480 --> 05:50.415
♪ you dreamer ♪

05:56.490 --> 05:59.891
- You're sure you're all right?
- I told ya, I'm fine.

06:03.697 --> 06:05.663
- Hey, um...

06:05.699 --> 06:06.865
Maybe I could take a look
at him.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.700
I work with horses.

06:08.835 --> 06:10.468
- I'll have him ready
for the race.

06:10.537 --> 06:13.004
- It's more your day-to-day
that I'm worried about.

06:13.006 --> 06:15.140
You or butch could be
seriously injured.

06:15.142 --> 06:16.941
Has this happened a lot before?

06:17.010 --> 06:19.544
- I know how to handle
my horse!

06:21.582 --> 06:23.715
(butch whinnies)
come on, butch.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.082
(hooves thud heavily)

06:25.119 --> 06:26.851
- (sighs)

06:26.920 --> 06:29.454
- You know, I think
you're right about butch

06:30.691 --> 06:33.024
And my grandpa knows it, too.

06:33.026 --> 06:34.992
They've been together
for 20 years.

06:35.028 --> 06:37.162
- Maybe it's time to retire
the horse.

06:37.297 --> 06:38.630
- Probably the end
of my grandpa, too.

06:38.765 --> 06:42.200
- But this isn't safe.
- Let me talk to him.

06:42.269 --> 06:44.169
I can usually get through
to him.

06:44.171 --> 06:45.637
- Thanks.

06:45.639 --> 06:48.039
(papers rustle)

06:51.845 --> 06:53.478
<i> (footsteps approach)</i>

06:54.782 --> 06:56.714
- Hey, sorry I'm late!
- Ah, no problem!

06:56.850 --> 06:58.716
I was just, uh, thinkin'
that there's probably room

06:58.786 --> 07:00.652
For a corporate banner
along the bottom

07:00.654 --> 07:02.520
Of the main stage.
- Let me guess, garland foods.

07:02.589 --> 07:04.523
- (chuckles) well, we are
the lead sponsor.

07:04.525 --> 07:06.124
- Fair enough.

07:06.193 --> 07:07.859
You know, we still need
an announcer for the event.

07:07.861 --> 07:09.428
- Oh, I was hoping
you might do it.

07:09.563 --> 07:11.129
- Me?
- Yeah.

07:11.198 --> 07:13.198
Who better than the mayor?
- Um, okay.

07:13.200 --> 07:14.732
Yeah, if you really want me to.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.668
- Great! You know, thanks, lou.

07:16.803 --> 07:19.270
You know, I, I really
appreciate you doing all this.

07:19.306 --> 07:20.672
I mean, ever since my brother,
evan,

07:20.674 --> 07:22.406
Started doing these
competitions,

07:22.443 --> 07:23.808
I've-I've wanted to put one on.

07:23.844 --> 07:26.011
- I'm happy to help!
It sounds like fun.

07:26.146 --> 07:28.547
- Yeah, well, I'd like
to take you to dinner.

07:29.683 --> 07:31.249
As a... Thank you.

07:31.285 --> 07:33.051
Uh, plus, I do still owe you
for saving my life

07:33.120 --> 07:34.486
On the cattle drive.

07:34.555 --> 07:36.321
- You would've done
the same for me

07:36.323 --> 07:37.489
If you knew how to throw
a rope.

07:37.558 --> 07:39.558
Both: (chuckle)

07:39.560 --> 07:42.760
- Uh, so, uh...
Well, how about Friday night?

07:42.796 --> 07:45.697
- Um... Maybe.
Let me just check my schedule.

07:45.766 --> 07:47.431
- 'kay!

07:47.468 --> 07:49.634
<i> Lyndy: I saw a giant</i>
<i> horse today!</i>

07:49.636 --> 07:51.503
- (laughs) yes, she did.
It was a clydesdale.

07:51.638 --> 07:53.371
- Oh!
- He's in that, uh,

07:53.507 --> 07:55.040
Logging competition.
- Right, right.

07:55.175 --> 07:58.843
Lou, you're... Really sinking
your teeth into this thing.

07:58.879 --> 08:01.513
- Well, with katie away
visiting her dad, I have time.

08:01.582 --> 08:03.314
Besides, it could be good
for tourism.

08:03.350 --> 08:04.783
That's one of the platforms
I ran on,

08:04.785 --> 08:06.384
So I want this to go well.

08:06.386 --> 08:08.386
Fred and I have some local
celebrities lined up.

08:08.388 --> 08:10.388
- Okay, so why do you need
celebrities

08:10.390 --> 08:11.723
For a lumberjack competition?

08:11.725 --> 08:13.258
- Uh, just to draw people out

08:13.327 --> 08:15.927
And to, uh, show how hard
this really is.

08:16.062 --> 08:17.662
- So, who've you got?

08:17.698 --> 08:20.165
- Sam langston's coming,
and caleb.

08:20.300 --> 08:22.601
- (chokes and coughs)
(fork clatters)

08:22.736 --> 08:25.403
Caleb? Why-why didn't
you ask me?

08:25.405 --> 08:27.539
- Actually, I was hoping you
and grandpa could be part of it

08:27.674 --> 08:30.174
As the officiants.
- I'm happy to help.

08:30.310 --> 08:31.943
- 'kay, this sounds really fun.
When is it?

08:32.078 --> 08:33.511
- Saturday.
- Oh good!

08:33.514 --> 08:35.313
'kay, I'm not leaving for
new york until Sunday night.

08:35.448 --> 08:36.948
So, I'm gonna take my camera,
of course,

08:37.083 --> 08:39.584
Show all my friends what I'm
trading in the big apple for.

08:41.088 --> 08:44.623
So, tell me where this giant
horse fits into all of this.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.490
- Two old-time loggers
go head-to-head

08:46.527 --> 08:48.960
Driving their draft horses
through an obstacle course.

08:49.095 --> 08:50.695
- Yeah, one of them's actually
a local guy.

08:50.731 --> 08:54.032
His name is al cotter.
He said he knows you, grandpa.

08:55.402 --> 08:57.836
- Yeah. From away back.

08:57.838 --> 09:00.305
- Well, you might have a chance
to get reacquainted.

09:00.374 --> 09:01.639
I'm hoping he'll bring
his horse over

09:01.675 --> 09:03.441
So I can work with it.

09:05.312 --> 09:06.578
- Okay.

09:07.648 --> 09:09.314
(crickets chirp)

09:09.383 --> 09:11.149
- So, fred and I were going
over some details

09:11.218 --> 09:13.184
For the event today

09:13.186 --> 09:14.786
And he asked me out to dinner.

09:14.788 --> 09:17.655
- Like a work dinner?
- No.

09:17.724 --> 09:20.391
- Ooh... Like a date!

09:20.460 --> 09:21.859
- No!

09:21.895 --> 09:23.394
At least I don't think so.

09:23.463 --> 09:24.929
- Come on, lou.
Two people out for dinner?

09:24.998 --> 09:28.133
That sounds very much
like a date.

09:28.268 --> 09:30.935
- Fred is a nice guy,
but we've tried this before

09:31.004 --> 09:33.071
And he bored me to tears.
- (laughs)

09:33.073 --> 09:35.139
- I mean, all he wants to talk
about is the high stakes,

09:35.208 --> 09:37.075
Fast-paced world of
the grocery store industry.

09:37.144 --> 09:40.411
- (sighs) okay.
What're you gonna tell him?

09:40.447 --> 09:42.413
- I dunno.
I'm in an awkward position.

09:42.482 --> 09:44.515
We're running the event
together.

09:46.587 --> 09:48.753
Why don't you come with me?
- (laughs) no.

09:48.789 --> 09:50.889
I'm not gonna be a third wheel
with fred.

09:51.024 --> 09:53.425
Why don't you just tell him
the truth?

09:53.427 --> 09:55.026
- That I don't wanna go out
with him?

09:55.161 --> 09:57.228
- That you're not exactly
single.

09:57.297 --> 09:58.630
- Amy.
- Come on.

09:58.765 --> 10:00.332
I can see what you're doing.

10:00.467 --> 10:01.899
You're throwing everything
into this event

10:01.969 --> 10:04.769
To distract yourself from...
Something?

10:05.839 --> 10:07.672
Like, maybe peter?

10:09.276 --> 10:11.643
What is going on with you guys?

10:11.712 --> 10:13.778
(fork scrapes and clanks)

10:14.848 --> 10:16.514
- It's complicated.

10:16.583 --> 10:17.915
(dish clanks)

10:19.052 --> 10:20.485
- (sighs)

10:20.487 --> 10:22.354
(thunder rumbles
in the distance)

10:24.124 --> 10:26.290
(thudding blow,
wood clatters)

10:27.427 --> 10:28.926
- (sighs)

10:31.064 --> 10:32.397
(hard thud, wood clatters)
- dad.

10:32.532 --> 10:34.199
You don't need to do that.

10:34.334 --> 10:36.034
We have enough firewood
for months.

10:36.169 --> 10:38.403
- That lumberjack competition?

10:38.538 --> 10:40.604
Thought I'd throw my hat
in the ring.

10:40.641 --> 10:43.274
- Are you serious? Those guys
are like half your age.

10:43.343 --> 10:44.743
- If you're talking
about sam and caleb,

10:44.745 --> 10:46.544
I think I'll be fine.

10:46.613 --> 10:48.079
(wood clatters)
- (sighs)

10:48.214 --> 10:49.948
(truck rumbles)

10:50.083 --> 10:54.585
♪♪♪

10:54.655 --> 10:56.053
(hooves clop)

10:58.091 --> 11:00.558
- It took some work,
but I convinced him.

11:00.627 --> 11:01.959
- How long's this gonna take?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.528
- It really depends.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.430
Maybe you could leave butch
here and come back later?

11:05.432 --> 11:08.132
- No, no, we got some forest
to clear this afternoon.

11:08.201 --> 11:09.934
It's a new contract.

11:09.936 --> 11:11.002
(footsteps squish)

11:11.137 --> 11:13.304
- Hey, grandpa!
You remember al?

11:13.373 --> 11:15.306
(thunder rumbles)

11:19.012 --> 11:21.146
- It's been a long time.

11:21.281 --> 11:22.847
- Sure has.

11:22.849 --> 11:26.050
- Maybe you guys could catch up
over coffee?

11:27.954 --> 11:30.521
- Maybe another time.
You comin'?

11:30.590 --> 11:33.758
- No, I'm gonna stay
and see if she needs a hand.

11:33.894 --> 11:35.526
- (sighs)

11:37.664 --> 11:39.464
(footsteps squish)

11:39.466 --> 11:43.835
♪♪♪

11:43.970 --> 11:46.137
(tire thumps on the ground)
thanks for stickin' around.

11:46.272 --> 11:47.772
I'd love it if you could
just ground drive him

11:47.808 --> 11:50.408
Around these barrels,
(harness clicks)

11:50.477 --> 11:52.744
Just like he does
through the trees.

11:52.813 --> 11:54.912
- (sighs) thank you.

11:56.082 --> 11:58.015
All right, butch.
(butch nickers)

11:58.051 --> 11:59.751
Let's go!
(hooves thud)

12:00.821 --> 12:03.120
- Good.
(harness jingles)

12:04.157 --> 12:05.957
- Attaboy. Yep.

12:06.092 --> 12:07.625
- That's it!

12:09.729 --> 12:11.162
Whoa, not too close.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

12:11.164 --> 12:12.964
(barrel clunks)

12:12.966 --> 12:14.565
(butch neighs)

12:14.601 --> 12:17.869
- Ho, ho, ho, you're okay.
- There's somethin' off.

12:17.938 --> 12:20.171
- (sighs) I have a hunch.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.773
Hey, buddy.

12:22.942 --> 12:24.776
(butch pants)

12:27.447 --> 12:28.846
(butch nickers)

12:30.050 --> 12:33.051
It's what I thought.
He's blind in his left eye.

12:33.186 --> 12:39.590
♪♪♪

12:43.864 --> 12:45.764
- So, he's gone completely
blind?

12:45.899 --> 12:47.598
- Just in his left eye.

12:47.667 --> 12:50.602
- I'm gonna have to retire you,
butch.

12:50.604 --> 12:52.570
I guess that means
I'm done, too.

12:52.639 --> 12:54.171
- Come on, grandpa.

12:54.207 --> 12:56.741
- Well, I'm not gonna go
through all the growing pains

12:56.743 --> 12:59.677
Of training a new horse
at my age.

12:59.746 --> 13:01.478
- I think that butch can
still log,

13:01.515 --> 13:04.081
But he'll need to do it
without blinders on.

13:04.117 --> 13:07.352
- Ah, nah, nah, nah,
that's not gonna work.

13:07.487 --> 13:10.021
Butch is a flighty horse;
he needs those blinders

13:10.023 --> 13:12.357
To keep him calm and focused
on the job.

13:12.492 --> 13:13.925
- I understand,
but without blinders,

13:14.060 --> 13:15.726
He'll have a greater range
of vision

13:15.796 --> 13:17.428
So he can navigate
through the forest

13:17.564 --> 13:20.031
Or through an obstacle course.
He'll be able to turn his head

13:20.166 --> 13:22.033
And see what's coming
with his good eye.

13:22.035 --> 13:24.102
- Look, grandpa,

13:24.237 --> 13:26.103
Give amy a chance.

13:26.173 --> 13:28.138
What's it gonna hurt, right?

13:30.677 --> 13:33.510
You know what I mean?
- Suit yourself.

13:33.547 --> 13:35.980
But I don't mean to make
a fool of myself

13:36.016 --> 13:38.883
In front of the whole town,
I'll tell ya that.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.454
- Gimme a second.
(footsteps crunch)

13:43.589 --> 13:49.127
♪♪♪

13:49.262 --> 13:51.329
(pestle grinds)

13:51.331 --> 13:54.065
- Ah, spartan's arthritis
acting up?

13:54.134 --> 13:56.400
- (sighs) I really don't know
what's going on.

13:56.469 --> 13:59.136
I'm trying some new supplements.

13:59.206 --> 14:02.139
- How'd it go with that
clydesdale?

14:02.209 --> 14:04.609
- He's blind in one eye.

14:04.678 --> 14:07.412
- I'm sorry to hear that.

14:07.547 --> 14:09.647
- Grandpa, what was that about
today?

14:09.716 --> 14:11.549
- What?
- You and al.

14:11.684 --> 14:13.351
You didn't exactly seem happy
to see each other

14:13.353 --> 14:15.152
After all these years.

14:15.188 --> 14:17.488
- Yeah, it's complicated.
- What happened?

14:18.725 --> 14:21.692
- It was a long time ago.

14:21.728 --> 14:23.628
- How did you guys know
each other?

14:23.763 --> 14:27.031
- Oh, he helped out here
for a bit.

14:28.167 --> 14:30.834
- Yeah, way back when my dad
was messed up

14:30.871 --> 14:33.837
And I was struggling to run
this place on my own.

14:33.874 --> 14:35.806
- Well, it sounds like
he was there for you

14:35.876 --> 14:38.076
During a tough time.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.944
- Like I said,
it was a long time ago.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.779
There's nothin' left
to say about it.

14:41.915 --> 14:44.048
- I'm sorry if I put you
in a tough spot.

14:44.117 --> 14:47.518
I, I didn't know there was--
- that's fine.

14:47.654 --> 14:50.387
Is, uh, he comin' back here
tomorrow?

14:50.423 --> 14:52.723
- I don't know. He's having
a hard time with this.

14:52.759 --> 14:55.225
I know that he has a strong
bond with his horse.

14:58.197 --> 15:00.731
(footsteps recede)

15:03.003 --> 15:04.936
- Really? I know I have a lot
of stuff to store,

15:05.005 --> 15:06.870
But that sounds expensive.

15:06.907 --> 15:09.540
Okay, would you mind
getting me a second quote?

15:09.609 --> 15:11.308
- Ow! Ooh, leg cramp.

15:12.478 --> 15:15.013
- Okay. Sorry, ezra,
I have to go.

15:15.015 --> 15:16.681
- (winces)

15:16.683 --> 15:18.649
- All right, stretch it out.

15:18.685 --> 15:20.485
- That's what I'm doin'.

15:20.620 --> 15:22.687
- Is this because of that
lumberjack competition?

15:22.689 --> 15:25.223
I don't know why you entered
that in the first place.

15:25.358 --> 15:27.158
- It's just a cramp.
I'll be fine.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.560
- Would you like me to run you
an epsom salt bath?

15:29.629 --> 15:32.096
- Epsom salt? What am I, 85?

15:32.098 --> 15:33.698
- Well, I don't know,
but this is what happens

15:33.700 --> 15:35.767
When you act like you're 25.

15:35.769 --> 15:38.669
♪♪♪

15:38.705 --> 15:40.838
(horses whinny)

15:44.577 --> 15:45.710
- This is gonna feel
a bit different,

15:45.845 --> 15:47.712
But I promise you'll be okay.

15:49.516 --> 15:50.948
(butch grunts nervously)
it's all right.

15:50.951 --> 15:53.518
He's just hookin' you up.
You do this all the time.

15:53.520 --> 15:55.019
(chain rattles,
butch grunts)

15:55.155 --> 15:57.154
- Whoa! It's all right!
(butch grunts nervously)

15:57.190 --> 15:59.257
Hey, you're okay.

15:59.259 --> 16:01.726
- That's not good.
- Well... (sighs)

16:01.795 --> 16:03.261
This is gonna take a few steps.

16:03.396 --> 16:06.064
First, we take off the blinders
so he can turn his head

16:06.066 --> 16:07.999
And have a bigger range
of vision

16:08.068 --> 16:11.002
And next, I have to work on
desensitizing him

16:11.071 --> 16:13.570
So he doesn't spook every time
he sees something behind him.

16:15.608 --> 16:17.608
- Thank you for giving this
a shot.

16:17.644 --> 16:19.544
I know my grandpa's difficult,

16:19.679 --> 16:21.612
And this horse means more
to him than he lets on.

16:21.614 --> 16:22.946
- I get it.

16:22.983 --> 16:24.882
- You know, I remember
when he first got him.

16:25.018 --> 16:27.017
I used to come out here
every summer as a kid.

16:27.019 --> 16:28.286
Still come out a couple times
a year,

16:28.421 --> 16:31.289
But... It's hard to see him
slowing down like this.

16:31.424 --> 16:33.357
(butch grunts)

16:33.393 --> 16:37.295
And, you know, him being
out here on his own.

16:39.332 --> 16:41.299
But...

16:41.301 --> 16:43.201
What's next, amy?

16:43.203 --> 16:45.236
- Well, I think I'd like to do
some work with him

16:45.305 --> 16:46.837
On my own for a bit,

16:46.873 --> 16:49.640
And then maybe you could
come back this afternoon?

16:49.642 --> 16:52.577
- Yeah. Let's do that.
(light pats)

16:52.712 --> 16:54.445
Okay.
- Thanks.

16:54.514 --> 16:56.447
(footsteps crunch softly)

16:57.517 --> 16:58.916
<i> (light knock)</i>
<i> fred: Hey, you!</i>

16:58.985 --> 17:00.651
- Oh, hey fred!
- You got some good news?

17:00.720 --> 17:03.387
- I do. I got clancy's pub
to put on a small event

17:03.456 --> 17:05.589
For everyone involved
in the lumberjack contest.

17:05.658 --> 17:07.525
Half off food and drinks
tonight.

17:07.594 --> 17:09.927
- Ah! That's fantastic!
(phone rings nearby)

17:09.929 --> 17:12.396
Um, but what about our dinner?

17:12.399 --> 17:14.065
I was hoping I could take you
out tonight?

17:14.134 --> 17:15.867
- Yeah, we could eat
at clancy's.

17:16.002 --> 17:17.801
- At a pub?
- Well, we are the team

17:17.837 --> 17:19.336
Putting this whole thing on
anyway.

17:19.372 --> 17:21.539
We should probably be there,
right?

17:21.541 --> 17:23.407
- Yeah...

17:23.443 --> 17:25.076
I guess you're right.

17:25.211 --> 17:27.478
Plus, we do make
a pretty great team, don't we?

17:27.613 --> 17:30.614
- Yeah. Yeah.
- All right, see ya tonight.

17:32.419 --> 17:33.884
- (sighs)

17:35.755 --> 17:38.489
Jack: How's it goin' with that
clydesdale today?

17:38.491 --> 17:40.958
- Oh, well, baby steps,

17:40.960 --> 17:43.094
But we'll get back at it
this afternoon.

17:43.229 --> 17:46.030
Al's grandson, finn,
he's giving me a hand.

17:46.032 --> 17:47.965
- Finn. He from around here?

17:48.101 --> 17:49.834
- No, he lives in saskatchewan,

17:49.903 --> 17:52.303
But, uh, he still visits al
every summer.

17:52.372 --> 17:54.172
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah.

17:54.174 --> 17:56.039
Seems like they're pretty close.

17:56.076 --> 17:57.642
It must be nice for al
to have someone around,

17:57.777 --> 18:00.178
Even if it is
for a short period of time.

18:00.313 --> 18:02.113
- Yeah, it must be.

18:02.182 --> 18:05.182
- You know, finn's really
all he has...

18:06.252 --> 18:08.119
Well, other than his horse,

18:08.188 --> 18:09.920
Which is kinda sad.
- Yeah, well,

18:09.956 --> 18:11.588
There's nothin' I can do
about that

18:11.624 --> 18:13.858
'cause sometimes, in life,
there are lines

18:13.860 --> 18:16.460
That can't be uncrossed.
(newspaper rustles)

18:16.529 --> 18:21.165
♪♪♪

18:25.472 --> 18:27.771
♪♪♪

18:27.841 --> 18:30.541
(truck rumbles,
rain puddles splash)

18:30.543 --> 18:32.410
(hooves clop)

18:32.412 --> 18:34.745
- Ho. It's okay.

18:34.747 --> 18:36.213
(feet splat lightly)

18:36.282 --> 18:39.617
- How's it goin'?
- Ah, it's okay.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.619
Spartan here isn't really
himself.

18:41.688 --> 18:43.688
You know, he's aging
and he has arthritis,

18:43.823 --> 18:47.424
But still, this sudden change
can't be good.

18:47.494 --> 18:50.161
- You know, he's not sound.
- Yes, he is.

18:50.230 --> 18:52.263
- No, what I mean is,
he, he seems sore.

18:52.398 --> 18:54.398
Maybe he needs corrective
shoeing.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.300
- My farrier's never
mentioned it,

18:56.369 --> 18:59.170
But I could ask him
next time he's out.

18:59.239 --> 19:00.971
- I don't think
you should wait.

19:01.007 --> 19:02.473
(gentle pats)

19:02.608 --> 19:05.376
I can do it for you.
- (sighs)

19:05.511 --> 19:08.179
- Look, I'm a...
I'm a farrier back home.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.080
I'm not trying to poach
any work,

19:10.116 --> 19:11.515
And I'm here anyway.

19:11.551 --> 19:13.184
- Okay, if you don't mind.

19:14.587 --> 19:16.587
- Plus, you've been helpin' out
butch so much,

19:16.722 --> 19:18.156
It's the least I can do.

19:18.291 --> 19:20.657
- Well, that's still a work
in progress, but...

19:20.693 --> 19:22.393
I'll show you
what we've accomplished.

19:22.395 --> 19:24.261
- All right.

19:24.330 --> 19:28.866
♪♪♪

19:28.935 --> 19:30.667
Amy: Good boy. It's okay.
- Good boy.

19:30.703 --> 19:33.537
(butch grunts)
- good boy.

19:33.573 --> 19:35.239
(flag flutters)
good boy.

19:36.476 --> 19:38.209
This morning when I started
doing this with the flag,

19:38.278 --> 19:40.110
Butch totally freaked out.

19:40.146 --> 19:41.479
He's so used to having
blinders on

19:41.481 --> 19:43.013
That anything in
his peripheral vision

19:43.049 --> 19:46.650
Just kinda makes him anxious
and nervous.

19:46.719 --> 19:49.319
- Well, he's... He's lookin'
pretty calm right now.

19:49.355 --> 19:51.289
- I'm gonna put the flag
right here,

19:51.291 --> 19:53.090
So he can see it,

19:53.159 --> 19:54.792
And I've added a new obstacle.

19:54.927 --> 19:58.262
This will mimic what butch
goes through in the forest.

19:58.398 --> 20:00.031
Wanna give it a go?

20:00.033 --> 20:01.498
- Let's do it.
- 'kay.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.634
- Alright. Walk on, boy!

20:03.703 --> 20:05.436
(clucks tongue)

20:05.438 --> 20:08.105
(butch grunts,
harness jingles)

20:08.107 --> 20:10.574
(hooves thud heavily)
good boy.

20:10.643 --> 20:12.510
Attaboy, butch.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.645
(harness jingles,
hooves thud heavily)

20:14.780 --> 20:16.647
- Nice!
- (butch snorts)

20:17.884 --> 20:19.916
- 'kay, do it!

20:19.953 --> 20:22.186
(butch whinnies nervously)

20:22.188 --> 20:23.321
- Come on, butch!

20:23.323 --> 20:26.257
(harness jingles,
butch snorts)

20:27.327 --> 20:29.126
Agghhh! So close!

20:29.195 --> 20:30.861
- It's okay!
I don't wanna push it.

20:30.897 --> 20:32.529
And I think with your grandpa
at the reins,

20:32.665 --> 20:34.232
He'll go right through.
- Huh?

20:34.367 --> 20:37.268
- I um... I just mean, like,
he is the pro, right?

20:37.403 --> 20:39.237
- Fair enough, fair enough.
- (chuckles)

20:39.372 --> 20:41.505
- So, is he gonna be good to go
this weekend?

20:41.541 --> 20:44.008
- Yeah. Yeah, he should be.

20:44.143 --> 20:45.676
- Wow.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.878
You really are
the miracle girl, huh?

20:49.415 --> 20:51.816
- (chuckles)
- yeah, I, I googled you.

20:51.951 --> 20:53.917
(harness wood and chain rattle)

20:54.988 --> 20:57.088
(finn and amy chuckle)

20:57.090 --> 20:58.489
(trailer door clunks shut)

20:58.558 --> 21:00.691
- So, just remember, when you
come close to an obstacle,

21:00.826 --> 21:02.693
You wanna pull on that rein
and turn his head,

21:02.695 --> 21:04.161
So he can see what's coming.

21:04.230 --> 21:05.963
- Yeah, yeah, I get it.

21:06.032 --> 21:08.098
- You shoulda see him, grandpa.

21:08.134 --> 21:10.434
He was doing great
without the blinders.

21:10.436 --> 21:13.037
- Yeah, but pressure
of competition,

21:13.039 --> 21:15.372
That's a whole other thing.

21:15.441 --> 21:17.408
(footsteps thud)

21:18.645 --> 21:20.177
- I'm gonna stick around
and uh...

21:20.246 --> 21:21.279
Take a look at amy's horse.

21:21.414 --> 21:24.114
- Yeah. Um, I'll go get spartan
ready.

21:25.718 --> 21:28.118
(footsteps recede)

21:30.657 --> 21:32.456
(birds chirp)

21:34.460 --> 21:37.361
- You come to throw me
off the property?

21:37.497 --> 21:39.996
Isn't that what you said you'd
do if I ever came back here?

21:40.033 --> 21:42.533
- I think I mighta used some
stronger language than that.

21:42.602 --> 21:45.536
- Yeah, and a couple of
haymakers if memory serves.

21:47.740 --> 21:50.875
All these years,
I can see it in your eyes -

21:50.877 --> 21:52.310
You still hold a grudge.

21:52.445 --> 21:55.011
- You and I, we were friends.

21:56.049 --> 21:58.281
- You and lyndy were hardly
even dating!

21:58.318 --> 22:00.284
- That's bull and you know it!

22:00.286 --> 22:02.086
I already bought her a ring!

22:02.088 --> 22:04.355
- Yeah, but ya didn't put it
on her finger yet!

22:07.226 --> 22:09.327
Ah... I asked her out,
she said no.

22:10.596 --> 22:13.364
What's the big deal?
- You kept asking.

22:13.499 --> 22:15.566
That's what the big deal is,

22:15.568 --> 22:17.768
You kept asking
'til I had to step in

22:17.770 --> 22:20.371
And give you the answer.
- Yeah.

22:21.641 --> 22:24.041
(footsteps recede)

22:29.215 --> 22:31.048
- I'm building him a bar shoe.

22:31.050 --> 22:33.451
This should help
with his arthritis pain.

22:33.586 --> 22:36.120
(tools clang gently)

22:36.122 --> 22:37.421
(flame hisses)

22:37.457 --> 22:40.457
(metallic scrape,
forge door creaks)

22:40.526 --> 22:44.028
(tongs clink,
door creaks shut)

22:44.030 --> 22:45.295
(tools rattle)

22:45.365 --> 22:47.097
(hissing)

22:47.133 --> 22:48.699
(door creaks open)

22:50.103 --> 22:53.069
(clamp clangs,
door creaks shut)

22:53.106 --> 22:55.105
(hammer clanks)

22:55.108 --> 22:59.710
♪♪♪

22:59.712 --> 23:02.813
(hammer clatters,
wire brush scrapes)

23:02.882 --> 23:04.382
(shoe hisses,
water splashes)

23:06.018 --> 23:08.084
(pritchel clanks,
hammer clangs)

23:08.121 --> 23:13.624
♪♪♪

23:13.759 --> 23:15.426
- No matter times I see it,

23:15.495 --> 23:18.396
I just love watching
this process.

23:18.531 --> 23:20.431
- You're not the first one
who's told me that.

23:20.500 --> 23:22.299
- (chuckles) my husband used
to say

23:22.435 --> 23:24.101
It was almost meditative
to him.

23:24.170 --> 23:26.036
He was a vet.

23:26.038 --> 23:27.638
- Yeah, I see the sign
on the barn.

23:27.640 --> 23:29.339
You guys are partners, too?

23:29.409 --> 23:31.842
- Yeah, we were.

23:31.977 --> 23:33.511
Ty passed away almost
two years ago.

23:33.513 --> 23:35.245
- (spartan nickers)

23:36.315 --> 23:37.415
- I'm sorry.

23:39.085 --> 23:41.051
- I can't even believe
it's been that long.

23:41.053 --> 23:43.454
You know, time just
sorta rolls by.

23:44.557 --> 23:47.925
You know, you go through
your daily routine.

23:47.994 --> 23:49.726
- Put the blinders on?

23:49.762 --> 23:51.996
- (sighs) exactly.

23:52.131 --> 23:53.431
<i> 'cause if you look at</i>
<i> the bigger picture</i>

23:53.566 --> 23:55.666
You know you're probably
gonna get spooked.

23:55.735 --> 23:57.635
- And when you start moving
forward,

23:57.637 --> 24:00.270
Allow yourself to have fun
and be happy,

24:00.339 --> 24:02.405
You start feeling guilty.

24:02.442 --> 24:03.874
- Yeah.

24:03.876 --> 24:06.743
- But you can't stay in
that place too long, amy.

24:06.779 --> 24:08.778
You're not supposed to feel
guilty about being happy.

24:10.116 --> 24:12.683
- So, it's time to take
the blinders off?

24:12.752 --> 24:14.652
- Yeah, maybe.

24:16.322 --> 24:17.488
- (snorts softly)

24:17.557 --> 24:20.691
♪♪♪

24:20.826 --> 24:22.759
<i> (screen door clicks open)</i>

24:22.761 --> 24:25.829
(items thunk,
footsteps approach)

24:25.832 --> 24:28.164
Oh, you're goin' out with fred.

24:28.201 --> 24:29.966
- It's more of a business thing
now,

24:30.002 --> 24:32.503
But I still don't feel right
about it.

24:32.572 --> 24:35.105
Amy, please come with me. When
was the last time you went out?

24:35.174 --> 24:36.640
- (sighs)
- you need to have some fun!

24:36.709 --> 24:39.776
- Hmm. Oh yeah, you,
fred, and me.

24:39.812 --> 24:42.246
- Sam and caleb might be there.

24:42.381 --> 24:44.215
Please?

24:46.752 --> 24:48.486
- Okay, fine, I'll come.
- Really?

24:48.621 --> 24:50.420
- Yeah, you're right,
it might be fun.

24:50.490 --> 24:52.156
- Yeah, exactly.
Okay, great, let's go,

24:52.158 --> 24:53.456
'cause I'm gonna be late.

24:53.493 --> 24:55.425
- Uh, can I at least get
cleaned up first?

24:55.461 --> 24:57.861
- Fine! Fine, but hurry up,
before you change your mind!

24:57.930 --> 24:59.497
(sighs)

24:59.632 --> 25:02.999
(country music plays,
crowd chatters)

25:03.035 --> 25:05.836
Bartender: Hey, lou!
- Oh!

25:05.838 --> 25:09.005
(patrons chatter,
music plays)

25:09.041 --> 25:11.308
- Hey!
- Oh!

25:11.377 --> 25:14.411
Uh, hey! I, uh, I got us
the best table in the house.

25:14.413 --> 25:17.014
- Great. Uh, look who decided
to tag along.

25:17.083 --> 25:19.182
- Hi, fred.
- Oh, hey, amy!

25:19.252 --> 25:21.285
Uh... This is a nice surprise.

25:22.955 --> 25:25.355
Uh, have a, have a seat.
- Great!

25:27.093 --> 25:29.560
- Uh, well you can have
one of these.

25:29.629 --> 25:31.428
- Now, what're you doin'
hoggin'

25:31.497 --> 25:32.829
The two best looking women
in the bar, huh?

25:32.899 --> 25:34.431
- Look, a little respect, evan.

25:34.567 --> 25:36.466
This is the mayor of hudson,
lou fleming.

25:36.502 --> 25:38.902
- Oh. Evan garland.
Pleased to meet you.

25:38.971 --> 25:41.471
- Oh, wait a second.
You're not his...

25:41.507 --> 25:44.708
- Oh, yes. Yes, his younger,
more handsome brother.

25:44.710 --> 25:48.011
- (chuckles)
- and who might you be?

25:48.080 --> 25:50.914
- Uh, I'm the mayor's sister,
amy.

25:50.950 --> 25:53.984
- Oh, nice to meet you.
- You too.

25:53.986 --> 25:57.187
- (sighs) well, you don't mind
if I join.

25:57.323 --> 26:00.991
