- (laughs)
- oh, hey al!

39:13.118 --> 39:15.118
Hey! Great job today.

39:15.120 --> 39:16.353
- Yeah.
- Thanks again for coming out.

39:16.488 --> 39:18.021
- Yeah.

39:19.524 --> 39:21.391
If you're expecting
an apology from me,

39:21.460 --> 39:23.226
You're not gonna get one.

39:23.228 --> 39:25.194
- I don't expect
anything from you.

39:27.466 --> 39:29.265
(footsteps recede)

39:29.334 --> 39:30.699
- Grandpa, what?

39:31.770 --> 39:33.335
- I'll see ya at home.

39:33.372 --> 39:34.804
Fred: All right,
just gimme a minute.

39:34.939 --> 39:36.539
Man: You got it.
- (sighs)

39:36.541 --> 39:40.009
- Uh, hey.
- Hey! Uh, great event today.

39:40.045 --> 39:42.011
- Oh yeah. No, I'm really glad
we did this together.

39:42.013 --> 39:44.013
- Yeah, me too.
- I mean, to be honest,

39:44.082 --> 39:47.016
Working with you is what made
me really want to do this.

39:47.085 --> 39:48.818
- Oh, I see.
- Um, listen, uh,

39:48.820 --> 39:52.355
You know, about last night--
- it's no big deal.

39:52.357 --> 39:54.424
- Aw, come on, lou,
it was a debacle.

39:54.493 --> 39:56.225
- Maybe a little bit.

39:56.261 --> 39:58.761
- Yeah, thanks for saving
my life, again.

39:58.830 --> 40:02.031
You know, I'm thinkin' the, uh,
the next fleming-garland outing

40:02.033 --> 40:05.168
Should probably be a duo.
Like... A date.

40:05.303 --> 40:07.904
- (sighs) look, fred, I...

40:07.973 --> 40:09.572
I think you're a really
nice guy, I do--

40:09.641 --> 40:11.240
- Uh-oh.
- But...

40:11.276 --> 40:12.709
- I see where this is going.
- (sighs)

40:12.711 --> 40:15.512
My status is just a bit
complicated at the moment.

40:15.647 --> 40:18.113
That's the truth.
- Okay, what does that mean?

40:18.150 --> 40:22.285
- (sighs) it means that despite
my attempts to distract myself

40:22.287 --> 40:26.022
From that very complicated
situation,

40:26.091 --> 40:28.525
There is someone else
in my life.

40:28.527 --> 40:30.259
- Well...

40:30.295 --> 40:32.795
Whoever's in the picture,

40:32.864 --> 40:34.531
He's one lucky guy.

40:34.533 --> 40:36.533
- (sighs)

40:36.668 --> 40:39.469
(birds chirp,
footsteps recede)

40:39.538 --> 40:41.604
- (sighs)

40:41.606 --> 40:45.140
♪♪♪

40:45.177 --> 40:47.343
- Oh!
- Oh...

40:47.412 --> 40:50.079
- Tsk.
- Oh! Ooh.

40:50.148 --> 40:52.682
- Oh, you don't know
how it feels. Agh!

40:52.684 --> 40:54.751
- (chuckles) do you want me to
run you that epsom salt bath?

40:54.753 --> 40:56.486
- Bring it on!
- Yeah.

40:57.689 --> 40:59.421
- Yeah. Right there. Thanks.

40:59.458 --> 41:01.224
- You were incredible
out there today...

41:01.359 --> 41:03.226
For an old guy.
- (sighs)

41:03.295 --> 41:05.761
- I'm sure that caleb and sam
are feeling way worse

41:05.797 --> 41:07.563
Than you are.
- I hope so.

41:07.632 --> 41:10.900
- You did kick their butts.
- I actually did, didn't I?

41:11.035 --> 41:13.570
- Mm-hmm.
- (laughs)

41:13.572 --> 41:16.572
- So, are you gonna tell me
what this is all about?

41:16.641 --> 41:19.108
- What do ya mean?
- This whole lumberjack thing?

41:19.144 --> 41:20.710
- Ungh.
- Wouldn't have anything to do

41:20.779 --> 41:23.312
With my friend ezra, would it?

41:23.348 --> 41:26.215
- No! No, not really.

41:27.886 --> 41:29.919
No, I just wanted you to get
some good action shots

41:30.054 --> 41:31.587
Of the guy you left
new york for.

41:31.656 --> 41:33.322
- Ah, I knew it.

41:33.358 --> 41:34.924
I mean, I thought it was
pretty cute

41:35.059 --> 41:37.594
But, come on, by now
you've gotta know

41:37.596 --> 41:40.597
That when it comes to you
there's no competition.

41:40.599 --> 41:42.532
(lips smack gently)

41:44.669 --> 41:46.135
(ice pack thumps)
- forget the bath.

41:46.271 --> 41:48.470
I'm getting my strength back.

41:48.507 --> 41:49.939
(pained laugh)

41:53.411 --> 41:54.677
(grunts softly)

41:54.746 --> 41:55.878
- Does that hurt?
- When you--

41:55.881 --> 41:59.148
Yeah. (laughs)
- right there? Ow. Oh, oh...

41:59.283 --> 42:01.617
(hooves thud confidently)

42:02.820 --> 42:04.153
(spartan nickers)

42:04.222 --> 42:05.755
(hooves thud)

42:06.925 --> 42:08.691
- His shoes seem to be
agreeing with him.

42:08.693 --> 42:11.894
- That's an understatement.
He feels like my horse again.

42:11.897 --> 42:14.097
- That's why I love my job.

42:14.232 --> 42:15.565
New pair of shoes can make
all the difference

42:15.634 --> 42:17.833
In the world sometimes.
(spartan nickers)

42:17.869 --> 42:19.235
- (sighs) well, thank you.

42:19.304 --> 42:20.870
(chuckles)

42:21.005 --> 42:22.605
- If you have anymore work,
just let me know.

42:22.641 --> 42:24.640
- I think that might be a bit
of a long house call

42:24.676 --> 42:26.742
From saskatchewan.
(spartan grunts)

42:26.744 --> 42:28.311
- (chuckles) actually...

42:28.446 --> 42:30.313
I'm thinking about sticking
around for a little bit,

42:30.315 --> 42:33.049
Keep an eye on my grandpa.
- Well, in that case,

42:33.051 --> 42:35.552
I'll definitely throw some work
your way.

42:35.687 --> 42:37.320
- Thanks.

42:37.455 --> 42:39.656
I'm gonna need more
than just one client.

42:39.791 --> 42:41.924
- I'll spread the word.
- (chuckles)

42:41.927 --> 42:44.259
- And, uh, I just have to say
thank you

42:44.296 --> 42:46.362
For what you said
the other night,

42:46.497 --> 42:48.997
About taking the blinders off.

42:48.999 --> 42:51.701
I needed to hear that.
- Yeah, anytime.

42:51.836 --> 42:55.438
♪ there is a place to land ♪

42:57.809 --> 43:00.476
♪ I understand ♪

43:00.478 --> 43:02.145
- (sighs)

43:02.280 --> 43:04.079
What do you think, boy?

43:04.115 --> 43:06.683
Should we go for a real ride?

43:06.818 --> 43:08.618
(chuckles)

43:08.753 --> 43:12.554
♪♪♪

43:12.591 --> 43:16.058
♪ use the heartbeat inside you ♪

43:18.430 --> 43:20.496
♪ let the blood run ♪

43:20.498 --> 43:24.299
- Good boy.
♪ through your veins ♪

43:24.336 --> 43:28.237
♪ and if you can just hold on ♪

43:30.942 --> 43:33.442
♪ we will find a way ♪

43:35.313 --> 43:36.646
(hooves thud away gently)

